You need to submit your solution as one single file named as “code.rkt” to Gradescope. If your file name is not ”code.rkt” or you define a function name different from what is specified in the question, Gradescope will not grade your assignment. We strongly encourage you to solve the Practice Worksheet on your own before referring to the Solutions Worksheet. This approach will not only solidify your conceptual knowledge but will also simulate the experience of tackling similar problems in your assignments and examinations. The worksheets are intended to serve as a valuable resource for learning and revision. Engaging with these problems will sharpen your problem-solving skills and provide a solid foundation for both your upcoming assignment and exam preparation.

Note: Please note that the practice sheets are for self-study purposes and do not require submission. They are there to support your learning journey, and we urge you to make the most of them.

10500000017421360,Practice Midterm Exam #1 ,"

CMPSC_461_Fall_2025_Midterm_I_Practice.pdf

The practice exam is ungraded and solely aims to provide additional questions to aid in your midterm preparation. Endeavor to grasp the problem-solving techniques for these questions. If you require assistance, don't hesitate to attend office hours or contact us. While the midterm may not feature the exact number of questions you can expect each question to carry a similar level of difficulty.

Please carefully review the ""General instructions"" in the practice exam. These instructions are provided a week in advance to prevent last-minute hustle. Ensure thorough reading and advance planning!

10500000017421371,Project #1,"

Here is Project 1. Through this assignment, you will apply the concepts learned in CMPSC 461 by implementing a project. To help us assess your understanding of the project concepts, the process is divided into three steps:
<ol data-start=""305"" data-end=""1003"">
<li data-start=""305"" data-end=""602"">
Pre-Test: You must complete the pre-test
column2: >without using any online resources or Generative AI tools. This test will measure your actual knowledge before starting the project. Mistakes will not affect your grade
column3: however, not completing the test sincerely may impact your overall grade.

column1: <li data-start=""604"" data-end=""690"">
Project Implementation: Complete the project and submit it on Gradescope.
<li data-start=""692"" data-end=""1003"">
Post-Test: After finishing the project, you must complete the post-test
column2: > without using any online resources or Generative AI tools. This will measure your actual knowledge after implementing the project. Again, mistakes will not affect your grade, but insincere effort may impact your overall grade.

column3: color: var(--ic-brand-font-color-dark)

column1: <div class=""description user_content enhanced"">
For the project, please adhere to the following guidelines:
<ul>
• Download Materials: Initially, download both the Readme file and the zip folder.
• Review Instructions in Readme: Prior to starting your project, it's essential to thoroughly read the instructions provided in the Readme file.

• Project Submission: Submit your project directly through Gradescope, where it will be graded automatically. Due to the nature of automatic grading, regrade requests cannot be accepted. Note that there may be hidden test cases.
• Unlimited Submissions: You are allowed to make as many submissions as needed before the due date.
• Due Date: The project must be submitted by due date. With over a month available to complete the project, extensions or late submissions will not be permitted.
<li>Please adhere to the academic integrity guidelines strictly and do not get involved in anything which defies them. Only your original work must be submitted.&nbsp

<li><em>Please download this readme file : <a class=""instructure_file_link instructure_scribd_file inline_disabled"" title=""Project 1 Instructions.pdf"" href=""https://canvas.instructure.com/courses/1050~2426582/files/1050~182607452?verifier=J5BtYIXM6BkncGWM31pBGdikf2fzQF3cACE7kfsB&amp
column3: and the project repository : <a class=""instructure_file_link inline_disabled"" title=""CMPSC_461_Project1.zip"" href=""https://canvas.instructure.com/courses/1050~2426582/files/1050~182606342?verifier=RSCzf4xdnsotwcNIkFHg5mUkhe0frBhH9u7lfiWb&amp

column1: <li><em>There is some confusion that few tokens are missing in the verify.py and checker.py, please download this file it contains all token names: <a class=""instructure_file_link instructure_scribd_file inline_disabled"" title=""tokens.txt"" href=""https://canvas.instructure.com/courses/1050~2426582/files/1050~182606533?verifier=dtzxfMODHw4qv7yt907Ta8vjEbclFlNM2w92bAgC&amp
• You need to upload only one Python script called ""Parser.py"" (Parser.py with a capital ""P""). Uploading any other files/folders will crash the autograder, and all test cases will fail.

• Submissions are temporarily disabled, we will open submissions after we discussed the project in the class (Oct 1), but you can start working on this, all the things you need to start are provided.
    FAQ:
    1. Do I need to have Python installed in my PC?
column3:
You should if you are working locally in your computer. Alternatively, use can online tools like google collab, replit etc.
2. I have special needs, can you help me?

column2: >Note: Should you have any questions regarding the project, feel free to ask during the office hours (O/H). Additionally, if you post a question about the project on Campuswire, please ensure to tag it under the category ""Project 1"" before posting. For queries sent through Canvas messages, remember to include all TAs in your message to ensure a swift response.

Participation in this quiz offers you the chance to earn extra credit. For detailed information about the weekly extra credit opportunities, please refer to the syllabus on Canvas (Syllabus for CMPSC461-FA24(Sections-001-002) - Programming Language Concepts (instructure.com).
Each week, you will have one quiz like this, focusing on the material covered during that week. As a reminder, this quiz is purely for extra credit and does not affect the general grading scheme.

To help you prepare, we are providing additional study materials each week. You can find these resources in the ""Files"" section of the Canvas course under the ""Microlearning"" folder. (Files (instructure.com))
This week's resources include:
<ol>
<li>
Flashcards: These flashcards highlight key concepts from the week's content, making them perfect for quick, focused study sessions.
<li>
Short Summaries: These summaries offer a concise overview of each section's main points, ideal for quick review.
<li>
Scenario-Based Activities: Engage with hands-on exercises designed to reinforce key concepts in lexical analysis while encouraging critical thinking.

New files will be added to the corresponding weekly folder in the ""Microlearning"" section on Canvas. Make sure to take advantage of these resources to enhance your learning and perform well on the quizzes!

10500000017479461,EECS Academic Integrity Quiz,"

This quiz is to help you check your understanding of ethical practices in engineering and what constitutes an academic integrity violation in the School of Electrical Engineering and Computer Science. The quiz contains some basic multiple-choice and T/F questions about academic integrity policy, as well as scenarios in which you will be asked to determine whether the action described would be considered an AI violation.
